The paper proposes a method for learning data-driven representations that can generalize well even when trained on inherently biased data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions classification performance, which suggests that it may belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper leverages information theory and proposes an end-to-end optimization strategy, which suggests that it may belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) or information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.CV, cs.CR, and cs.IT.
